# Google Places API key — required.
#
# 1. Open https://console.cloud.google.com/google/maps-apis/credentials
# 2. Enable "Places API (New)" and "Geocoding API" on the project.
# 3. Create an API key. Restrict it to those two services.
# 4. Paste the key below, then save this file as `.env.local`.
#
# Your `.env.local` is gitignored. Treat the key like a password — Google bills
# the project that owns it, and Randort runs entirely on your machine, so the
# key never leaves your local environment unless you choose to deploy.
GOOGLE_PLACES_API_KEY=
